Leang Burung,,,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/88744-3.pdf,5,"and to island [35, 39]. The islands of the northern route were more densely forested and in the case of the larger islands like Sulawesi had a range of medium to large terrestrial game as seen in the faunal records from Leang Burung 2, Goa Topogaro 2 and Leang Sakapao 1 [37 , 40, 41]. In contrast, the southern Wallacean islands are distinguished by being depauperate in terrestrial fauna, although the larger southern islands, Flores, Alor and Timor",Leang Burung,duplicate,
Leang Sakapao,,,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/88744-3.pdf,5,"of the northern route were more densely forested and in the case of the larger islands like Sulawesi had a range of medium to large terrestrial game as seen in the faunal records from Leang Burung 2, Goa Topogaro 2 and Leang Sakapao 1 [37 , 40, 41]. In contrast, the southern Wallacean islands are distinguished by being depauperate in terrestrial fauna, although the larger southern islands, Flores, Alor and Timor had giant murids at the time of mode",Leang Sakapao,duplicate,
