Gua Metanduno,,,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/StencilsBoatsMunaIsland.pdf,11,"70 The Archaeology of Sulawesi terra australis 48 Gua Kabori Gua Kabori is located 25 m southeast from the Gua Metanduno site. The cave is dome-shaped with ledges along the wall. Its mouth faces west, and there is an ongoing process of stalactite and stalagmite formation. The term kabori translates to a cave with writing (or drawings). As",Gua Metanduno,duplicate,
