Liang Bua,,,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/WallaceaHumanMigration.pdf,5,"nducted in the islands of Flores, Alor, and Timor (mainly in Timor-Leste), and have so far discovered some early sites occupied by modern humans dating back to 44 and 42 ka [2, 21, 22]. The appearance of Homo sapiens at Liang Bua site in Flores Island (see Figure 1) could be as old as 50-48 ka [7], though there is no clear evidence of modern humans by this age yet. Since the site was occupied by Homo floresiensis, we need more solid data to conf",Liang Bua,duplicate,
Leang Sarru,,,,,data/google-drive-pdfs/WallaceaHumanMigration.pdf,5,"tes as old as 43 ka [4, 24], with the earliest 14C dates in South Sulawesi dated to 36 ka [25]. Other sites older than 30 ka along the northern routes are Golo Cave in Gebe Island ( Figure 1) dated to c. 36 ka [26, 27], Leang Sarru in the Talaud Islands ( Figures 1 and 2) dated to 35 ka [28 –32], and Bubog 1 in Mindoro Island ( Figure 1) dated to >35 ka [9, 33]. None of these sites produced early modern human fossil remains, however, if the U-seri",Leang Sarru,duplicate,
