Liang Lumba,,,,,"data/google-drive-pdfs/Painted Sites, Sacred Sites_NHT.pdf",215,"recently, relatively little research has been done in Southeast Asia, leaving one with the impression that there is little or no rock art in the region. Up until the 1980s, only a handful of sites were known, including Liang Lumba in Kalimantan [3], Khao Khian, Pha Mue Daeng and Tham Roob [5 –7] in Thailand, several Indonesian sites named by van Heekeren [8,9], Gua Tambun in Peninsular Malaysia [10,11], the Painted Cave (Gua Kain Hitam) in Malays",,overlap_with_existing,
